      "description": "If the JWT signing secret is a common dev placeholder (\"secret\", \"changeme\", \"your-secret-key\", etc.), an attacker can forge tokens at will. We try a pre-computed set of HS256 tokens, each signed with a common dev secret carrying admin claims; if any returns 200 with user data, the secret has been guessed.",
